name: Imperfection Beauty
description:
Inspired by invincible women, we build a broken naked cake that was concealed with sugar gumpaste flowers. But behind that gorgeous look, those flowers have meaning.

Myosotis represents the missed memory of protection and warmness inside her mother’s womb. Chrysanthemum represents sadness and suffering behind its beauty. Gladiolus symbolized strengths that forged through painful experiences. Papaver represents the peaceful life that all women deserve. Ulex popped up as a symbol of hope over sadness and grief.
